# CI Implementation Plan for chatlogtoeml
## Target: GitHub Actions (free tier, public repo)

---

## Overview

This plan produces two workflow files and one change to `pyproject.toml`.

**Files to create:**
- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — runs on every push/PR; jobs: lint, test, smoke, build
- `.github/workflows/security.yml` — runs nightly + on push to `main`; job: audit

**Files to modify:**
- `pyproject.toml` — add a `[dependency-groups]` dev group (PEP 735, supported by uv)

**Key design decisions:**
- This project uses `uv` with a committed `uv.lock`. All CI installs use
  `uv sync --frozen`, which verifies the lockfile is up-to-date and refuses to
  modify it. This is the correct CI posture.
- Dev tools (ruff, pip-audit) are added to a `[dependency-groups]` dev group so
  their versions are locked in `uv.lock`. They are invoked via `uv run` so the
  locked versions are used — not whatever happens to be latest.
- Action versions must be pinned to full 40-character SHA digests (see Step 5)
  to prevent supply chain attacks via tag hijacking.
- For a public repo, GitHub Actions minutes are unlimited; all jobs run on every
  push and PR.

---

## Step 1 — Add a dev dependency group to `pyproject.toml`

Open `pyproject.toml`. **After** the `[tool.setuptools.packages.find]` block, append:

```toml
[dependency-groups]
dev = [
  "ruff>=0.9",
  "pip-audit>=2.9",
]
```

`ruff` handles both linting and format-checking (replacing flake8 + isort + black
in a single tool). `pip-audit` scans dependency trees for known CVEs.

Do NOT add `mypy` at this time — the codebase has no type annotations and mypy
would produce noise. It can be added later if annotations are introduced.

---

## Step 2 — Regenerate `uv.lock`

Run this once locally after editing `pyproject.toml`:

```bash
uv lock
```

Commit both `pyproject.toml` and the updated `uv.lock` together.

---

## Step 3 — Create `.github/workflows/ci.yml`

Create the file at exactly that path with this content:

```yaml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: ["main", "feature/**"]
  pull_request:
    branches: ["main"]

# Restrict default token to read-only; each job grants only what it needs.
permissions:
  contents: read

jobs:

  # ── 1. Lint ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  lint:
    name: Lint (ruff)
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: astral-sh/setup-uv@v4
        with:
          enable-cache: true
          cache-dependency-glob: "uv.lock"

      # Install project + dev deps (ruff is in the dev group)
      - name: Install dependencies
        run: uv sync --frozen

      - name: Lint — ruff check
        run: uv run ruff check .

      - name: Lint — ruff format check
        run: uv run ruff format --check .

  # ── 2. Unit tests (matrix) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  test:
    name: Test (Python ${{ matrix.python-version }})
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    strategy:
      fail-fast: false
      matrix:
        python-version: ["3.9", "3.11", "3.12"]

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: astral-sh/setup-uv@v4
        with:
          enable-cache: true
          cache-dependency-glob: "uv.lock"
          python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: uv sync --frozen

      # Generate the synthetic DB fixtures that several tests depend on
      - name: Generate test fixtures
        run: |
          uv run python tools/generate_ios_smsdb_fixture.py
          uv run python tools/generate_macos_chatdb_fixture.py
          uv run python tools/generate_blob_case_fixtures.py

      - name: Run unit tests
        run: uv run python -m unittest discover -v

  # ── 3. Smoke tests ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  smoke:
    name: Smoke tests
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    needs: [test]   # only run if unit tests pass

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: astral-sh/setup-uv@v4
        with:
          enable-cache: true
          cache-dependency-glob: "uv.lock"

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: uv sync --frozen

      - name: Generate fixtures
        run: |
          uv run python tools/generate_ios_smsdb_fixture.py
          uv run python tools/generate_macos_chatdb_fixture.py

      - name: Smoke — db_to_eml (iOS sms.db)
        run: |
          mkdir -p /tmp/smoke_ios
          uv run bin/db_to_eml samples/ios/sms.db /tmp/smoke_ios \
            --clobber
          count=$(ls /tmp/smoke_ios/*.eml 2>/dev/null | wc -l)
          echo "iOS smoke: $count .eml file(s) produced"
          [ "$count" -gt 0 ] || (echo "ERROR: no .eml output" && exit 1)

      - name: Smoke — db_to_eml (macOS chat.db)
        run: |
          mkdir -p /tmp/smoke_macos
          uv run bin/db_to_eml samples/macos/chat.db /tmp/smoke_macos \
            --clobber
          count=$(ls /tmp/smoke_macos/*.eml 2>/dev/null | wc -l)
          echo "macOS smoke: $count .eml file(s) produced"
          [ "$count" -gt 0 ] || (echo "ERROR: no .eml output" && exit 1)

      - name: Smoke — json_to_eml (sample.ndjson)
        run: |
          mkdir -p /tmp/smoke_ndjson
          uv run bin/json_to_eml samples/ndjson/sample.ndjson /tmp/smoke_ndjson \
            --local-handle me --clobber
          count=$(ls /tmp/smoke_ndjson/*.eml 2>/dev/null | wc -l)
          echo "NDJSON smoke: $count .eml file(s) produced"
          [ "$count" -gt 0 ] || (echo "ERROR: no .eml output" && exit 1)

      - name: Smoke — chat_convert (Adium XML)
        run: |
          mkdir -p /tmp/smoke_adium
          uv run bin/chat_convert \
            'samples/adiumxml/theirscreenname (2007-03-25T12.31.28-0400).chatlog' \
            /tmp/smoke_adium --clobber
          count=$(ls /tmp/smoke_adium/*.eml 2>/dev/null | wc -l)
          echo "Adium smoke: $count .eml file(s) produced"
          [ "$count" -gt 0 ] || (echo "ERROR: no .eml output" && exit 1)

  # ── 4. Build verification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  build:
    name: Build sdist + wheel
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    needs: [test]

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: astral-sh/setup-uv@v4
        with:
          enable-cache: true
          cache-dependency-glob: "uv.lock"

      # Build without dev extras to confirm the runtime package is self-contained
      - name: Install runtime dependencies only
        run: uv sync --frozen --no-dev

      - name: Build sdist and wheel
        run: uv build

      # twine check validates PKG-INFO / METADATA formatting (no upload)
      - name: Validate dist metadata
        run: uv tool run twine check dist/*

      - name: Upload dist artifacts
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: dist
          path: dist/
          retention-days: 7
```

---

## Step 4 — Create `.github/workflows/security.yml`

Create the file at exactly that path with this content:

```yaml
name: Security audit

on:
  schedule:
    # Run nightly at 02:17 UTC (offset from :00 to reduce GitHub load spikes)
    - cron: "17 2 * * *"
  push:
    branches: ["main"]

permissions:
  contents: read

jobs:
  pip-audit:
    name: pip-audit (CVE scan)
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: astral-sh/setup-uv@v4
        with:
          enable-cache: true
          cache-dependency-glob: "uv.lock"

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: uv sync --frozen

      # Export the locked runtime deps to a requirements.txt, then audit them.
      # --no-dev excludes ruff/pip-audit themselves from the scan (reduces noise).
      - name: Export locked requirements
        run: uv export --frozen --no-dev -o /tmp/requirements-locked.txt

      - name: Run pip-audit
        run: |
          uv run pip-audit \
            --requirement /tmp/requirements-locked.txt \
            --output-format columns
```

---

## Step 5 — Pin action versions to SHA digests (supply chain hardening)

**This step is mandatory before merging.** GitHub Actions `@vN` tags can be moved
by the action maintainer to point to different (potentially malicious) code.
Pinning to a full 40-character SHA makes the workflow immutable.

### How to find the correct SHA

For each action reference in the YAML files (`actions/checkout@v4`,
`astral-sh/setup-uv@v4`, `actions/upload-artifact@v4`):

1. Go to the action's GitHub repository.
2. Click "Releases", find the latest release for the major version tag (e.g. `v4`).
3. Click the release commit link to open the commit page.
4. Copy the full 40-character commit SHA from the URL or "Copy SHA" button.

### Replace each `@vN` tag with `@<SHA>`

Example (do not use these — look up current values):

```yaml
# Before:
- uses: actions/checkout@v4
# After (example SHA — verify this yourself):
- uses: actions/checkout@11bd71901bbe5b1630ceea73d27597364c9af683  # v4.2.2
```

Include a `# vX.Y.Z` comment after each SHA so it remains human-readable.

Replace all three action references in both workflow files:
- `actions/checkout@v4`
- `astral-sh/setup-uv@v4`
- `actions/upload-artifact@v4`

### Automated alternative

Install `pin-github-actions` (or similar tooling) to do this automatically:

```bash
# Using pipx (does not need to be in this project's deps)
pipx run pin-github-actions .github/workflows/ci.yml
pipx run pin-github-actions .github/workflows/security.yml
```

---

## Step 6 — Add ruff configuration to `pyproject.toml`

Append this block to `pyproject.toml` to configure ruff for the codebase.
The settings are chosen to be non-intrusive for an existing project:

```toml
[tool.ruff]
target-version = "py39"
line-length = 100

[tool.ruff.lint]
# E/W = pycodestyle, F = pyflakes, I = isort, UP = pyupgrade (auto-fix)
select = ["E", "W", "F", "I", "UP"]
# Ignore line-length in existing docstrings/comments; fix code >= 100 chars
ignore = ["E501"]

[tool.ruff.lint.isort]
known-first-party = ["chatlogtoeml"]
```

After adding this, run `uv run ruff check .` locally before the first push to
see what violations exist. Fix errors (E/F/W); format issues can be
auto-fixed with `uv run ruff format .` and `uv run ruff check --fix .`.

---

## Step 7 — Verify locally before pushing

Run the full local equivalent of what CI will run:

```bash
# 1. Confirm lockfile is consistent after pyproject.toml changes
uv sync --frozen

# 2. Lint
uv run ruff check .
uv run ruff format --check .

# 3. Generate fixtures
uv run python tools/generate_ios_smsdb_fixture.py
uv run python tools/generate_macos_chatdb_fixture.py
uv run python tools/generate_blob_case_fixtures.py

# 4. Unit tests
uv run python -m unittest discover -v

# 5. Quick smoke (ios only)
mkdir -p /tmp/smoke_ios
uv run bin/db_to_eml samples/ios/sms.db /tmp/smoke_ios --clobber
ls /tmp/smoke_ios/*.eml

# 6. Build
uv build
uv tool run twine check dist/*
```

---

## Step 8 — Commit and push

```bash
git add pyproject.toml uv.lock \
        .github/workflows/ci.yml \
        .github/workflows/security.yml
git commit -m "Add GitHub Actions CI and nightly security audit"
git push
```

After the push, open the repository on GitHub, click the "Actions" tab, and
confirm all jobs are green. The security workflow will also be visible under
"Scheduled" workflows and will first run at 02:17 UTC.

---

## Expected job run times (free tier, ubuntu-latest)

| Job              | Est. runtime |
|------------------|--------------|
| lint             | ~45 s        |
| test (3.9)       | ~60 s        |
| test (3.11)      | ~55 s        |
| test (3.12)      | ~55 s        |
| smoke            | ~90 s        |
| build            | ~45 s        |
| pip-audit (night)| ~60 s        |

Total per push: ~6 minutes elapsed (lint + test matrix + smoke + build run in parallel).
Public repo minutes on GitHub free tier are unlimited, so there is no cost concern.

---

## Notes and decisions not made here

- **Codecov / coverage upload:** Not included. If coverage is wanted, add
  `coverage run -m unittest discover -v && coverage xml` and the
  `codecov/codecov-action` step to the test job.
- **mypy:** Not included. The codebase has no type annotations. Add it to the dev
  group and a dedicated `typecheck` job only after annotations are introduced.
- **Dependabot for actions:** Consider adding `.github/dependabot.yml` to keep
  action SHA pins fresh automatically:
  ```yaml
  version: 2
  updates:
    - package-ecosystem: "github-actions"
      directory: "/"
      schedule:
        interval: "weekly"
  ```
- **Branch protection:** After CI is green, enable "Require status checks to pass
  before merging" on the `main` branch in the repository settings, and require
  all four CI jobs: `lint`, `test (3.9/3.11/3.12)`, `smoke`, `build`.
